30
00:02:09,276 --> 00:02:10,607
Can't hang about.

31
00:02:10,944 --> 00:02:14,880
Apparently, they have one of these
every 20 minutes at this time of year.

32
00:02:15,682 --> 00:02:18,378
- Well, who's going to tell her?
- I'll go.

33
00:02:28,762 --> 00:02:30,957
What was that about the music?

34
00:02:31,131 --> 00:02:34,658
Well, when I was 15,
we lived near a dance hall...

35
00:02:34,935 --> 00:02:36,630
...and there was a band.

36
00:02:37,070 --> 00:02:39,937
And some girls used to sing a song called...

37
00:02:40,907 --> 00:02:43,603
I'll Be Glad When You're Dead
You Rascal, You.

38
00:02:43,677 --> 00:02:45,167
Never heard of it.

39
00:02:45,445 --> 00:02:48,380
When they started to play that
rubbish in the crematorium...

40
00:02:48,448 --> 00:02:50,609
...I shut my ears and that's what I heard.

41
00:02:50,684 --> 00:02:53,380
I'll Be Glad When You're Dead
You Rascal, You.

42
00:02:53,487 --> 00:02:56,081
I got a fit of the giggles,
and I'm very ashamed.

43
00:02:56,156 --> 00:02:58,090
Was grandpa a rascal?

44
00:02:58,892 --> 00:02:59,881
No.

45
00:03:01,294 --> 00:03:02,761
He was anything but.

46
00:03:03,530 --> 00:03:06,431
- You may disagree, but...
- No, I know what you mean.

47
00:03:06,666 --> 00:03:08,691
But he was kind, wasn't he?

48
00:03:09,002 --> 00:03:12,460
I mean, he would always pat me
on the head and give me a pound.

49
00:03:12,706 --> 00:03:14,537
You and me both, sweetheart.

50
00:03:15,308 --> 00:03:17,970
You all right now?
Can you cope with the wake?

51
00:03:18,144 --> 00:03:19,771
Of course I can, dear.

52
00:03:20,847 --> 00:03:22,610
Lead me to the golfers.

53
