"I'm feeling fine again

511
00:38:22,280 --> 00:38:25,249
"I'm going to rise and shine again

512
00:38:25,350 --> 00:38:29,013
"I've almost lost my mind again

513
00:38:29,587 --> 00:38:32,249
"Taking a chance on love

514
00:38:33,157 --> 00:38:36,320
"Boy, I'm booked again"

515
00:38:37,395 --> 00:38:40,831
- She's still terrific.
- I know, she was my second wife.

516
00:38:41,165 --> 00:38:42,655
- Sorry?
- Nothing.

517
00:38:43,768 --> 00:38:46,293
"Taking a chance on love

518
00:38:47,572 --> 00:38:50,769
"This game I'm having a crack

519
00:38:51,509 --> 00:38:54,137
"Needs good love from me

520
00:38:55,480 --> 00:38:57,243
"So I'm taking a whack

521
00:38:58,850 --> 00:39:01,182
"At any black cat I see

522
00:39:02,920 --> 00:39:05,855
"On the breeze again

523
00:39:06,124 --> 00:39:08,820
"And though I'd love to please again

524
00:39:09,494 --> 00:39:15,490
"I'm saving your reprieves again

525
00:39:18,136 --> 00:39:20,366
"So ring down the curtain

526
00:39:20,471 --> 00:39:22,029
"It's love for certain

527
00:39:22,106 --> 00:39:26,406
"I'm taking a chance on love

528
00:39:29,681 --> 00:39:32,081
"Taking another chance on love"

529
00:39:40,692 --> 00:39:42,182
Thank you very much.

530
00:39:43,995 --> 00:39:45,462
You don't play anymore?

531
00:39:45,530 --> 00:39:47,862
No, I retired when all the trumpet players...

532
00:39:47,932 --> 00:39:50,526
...came home from the war
wanting their jobs back.

533
00:39:50,601 --> 00:39:53,331
The men. You know what I mean.

534
00:39:53,404 --> 00:39:55,429
Besides, it was hard on the lips, babe.

535
00:39:56,140 --> 00:39:58,734
- I stick to the singing.
- No more triple tonguing?

536
00:39:59,744 --> 00:40:02,611
That ceased to be your business long ago.

537
00:40:03,715 --> 00:40:06,582
- Is it your business now, Elizabeth?
- Absolutely not.

538
00:40:06,651 --> 00:40:08,949
Our purpose is to
get the band together again.

539
00:40:09,220 --> 00:40:10,585
You got a gig?

540
00:40:10,888 --> 00:40:12,446
First of next month.

541
00:40:12,657 --> 00:40:13,749
What is it?

542
00:40:15,793 --> 00:40:18,387
It's my granddaughter's school dance.

543
00:40:20,732 --> 00:40:22,563
A school dance?

544
00:40:23,434 --> 00:40:26,130
I never played school dances
even when I was at school.

545
00:40:27,105 --> 00:40:29,665
- We're starting rehearsals next week.
- Sweetheart.

546
00:40:30,475 --> 00:40:33,444
I have sung for my supper
for half a lifetime...

547
00:40:33,511 --> 00:40:36,412
...and I've done it all without rehearsals.

548
00:40:36,547 --> 00:40:39,516
I turn up at the gig,
I moan about the piano...

549
00:40:39,684 --> 00:40:43,711
...I hand out the parts,
I count the guys in, and I get on with it.

550
00:40:44,088 --> 00:40:45,680
Make it a social call.

551
00:40:45,757 --> 00:40:48,191
- Come and see the girls.
- There'll be a fight.

552
00:40:48,259 --> 00:40:50,386
Well, come and see the fight.

553
00:40:53,698 --> 00:40:56,030
Do yourself a favor, babe.
Get rid of this man.

554
00:40:56,534 --> 00:40:58,229
Why, what's wrong with him?

555
00:40:58,302 --> 00:41:00,270
Please welcome Gwen back to the stage.

556
00:41:00,338 --> 00:41:02,431
Ask him about the roses.

557
00:41:06,978 --> 00:41:09,412
A one, a two, a one, two, three.

558
00:41:20,057 --> 00:41:22,389
All right, stop!

559
00:41:24,462 --> 00:41:27,795
- Terrible. Somebody was out of tune.
- We were all out of tune.

560
00:41:27,865 --> 00:41:29,594
I was in tune.

561
00:41:29,934 --> 00:41:32,368
Yes, but you still can't count to four.

562
00:41:32,970 --> 00:41:34,369
How'd it sound for you?

563
00:41:34,605 --> 00:41:36,596
I can see why the Germans bombed you.

564
00:41:37,175 --> 00:41:39,336
We've got no top line, no bottom line...

565
00:41:39,577 --> 00:41:41,545
...and there's bugger-all in the middle.

566
00:41:41,612 --> 00:41:44,376
- I know we can't have a double bass...
- Why not?

567
00:41:44,448 --> 00:41:46,245
There's one in the picture.

568
00:41:49,086 --> 00:41:51,077
That's Madeleine. She's French.

569
00:41:51,155 --> 00:41:54,249
She left the band and went back to Paris
to join the Resistance.

570
00:41:54,358 --> 00:41:56,883
- That's the last we've heard of her.
- That's sad.

571
00:41:57,628 --> 00:41:59,858
We'll have to manage
without her, I suppose.

572
00:42:00,298 --> 00:42:01,731
That's not good enough.

573
00:42:02,099 --> 00:42:04,932
You were war heroes.
I think you should try harder.

574
00:42:13,477 --> 00:42:14,671
Where are you going?

575
00:42:22,720 --> 00:42:23,709
No.

576
00:42:26,824 --> 00:42:28,223
Thank you, dear.

577
00:42:36,834 --> 00:42:38,961
What are you collecting for?

578
00:42:39,136 --> 00:42:42,537
The poor, the sick, and the dispossessed.
You don't qualify.

579
00:42:44,208 --> 00:42:46,733
Could the poor, the sick
and the dispossessed...

580
00:42:46,811 --> 00:42:49,143
...use £259?

581
00:42:50,648 --> 00:42:53,947
If you take this slip into that betting shop...

582
00:42:54,051 --> 00:42:56,679
...they will give you £259.

583
00:42:57,855 --> 00:42:59,482
- I don't gamble.
- You haven't.

584
00:42:59,557 --> 00:43:02,321
I was the one that gambled
on a double at Newmarket.

585
00:43:02,393 --> 00:43:03,883
The wages of sin.

586
00:43:04,195 --> 00:43:05,662
You have my word.

587
00:43:05,930 --> 00:43:09,024
The races on this occasion were not fixed.

588
00:43:10,968 --> 00:43:12,526
You know I can't take this.

589
00:43:13,104 --> 00:43:15,538
Remember the parable of the talents?

590
00:43:16,207 --> 00:43:17,902
Matthew, chapter 25?

591
00:43:18,743 --> 00:43:21,007
"He that had received the five talents...

592
00:43:21,078 --> 00:43:23,945
"...traded with them and
made with them five more."

593
00:43:24,115 --> 00:43:28,051
And the Lord said, "Well done,
thou good and faithful servant."

594
00:43:28,953 --> 00:43:32,821
Now, that's got to be an even money shot
whichever way you look at it.

595
00:43:32,890 --> 00:43:35,984
If I take this, what do I have to do?

596
00:43:37,328 --> 00:43:40,593
Whatever the good Lord
in his infinite wisdom tells you.

597
00:43:41,899 --> 00:43:45,130
I hope that he would suggest
you multiply your talent...

598
00:43:46,470 --> 00:43:48,995
...and spread its sweetness
across all the earth.

599
00:44:01,519 --> 00:44:04,147
Stop! Stop, stop, stop, stop.

600
00:44:04,822 --> 00:44:06,153
Oh, dear.

601
00:44:06,891 --> 00:44:08,222
It's amazing.

602
00:44:08,326 --> 00:44:10,726
The more we rehearse,
the worse we sound.

603
00:44:11,028 --> 00:44:12,256
Well?

604
00:44:13,164 --> 00:44:15,689
The committee meets tonight.
What do I tell them?

605
00:44:15,766 --> 00:44:17,825
Tell them we need a good lead trumpet...

606
