well, that's our little attempt to have...

694
00:48:51,575 --> 00:48:54,442
...one last gamble before we shuffle off...

695
00:48:55,045 --> 00:48:57,809
...to the great Metropole
Ballroom in the sky.

696
00:49:00,918 --> 00:49:02,647
That was very impressive.

697
00:49:03,053 --> 00:49:05,248
When did you win the Military Cross?

698
00:49:05,656 --> 00:49:07,783
I forget exactly, 1963-4.

699
00:49:07,858 --> 00:49:08,950
Which war?

700
00:49:09,526 --> 00:49:12,120
Actually, I won it at poker
from an old war hero...

701
00:49:12,196 --> 00:49:13,686
...down on his luck.

702
00:49:13,764 --> 00:49:15,698
- That's despicable.
- I was desperate.

703
00:49:15,766 --> 00:49:17,529
I want your family to like me.

704
00:49:20,237 --> 00:49:22,432
What the hell is that?

705
00:49:23,440 --> 00:49:26,307
This belongs to Sid.

706
00:49:27,111 --> 00:49:28,908
