00:52:49,179 --> 00:52:51,909
- This will help.
- Thank you so much. Thank you.

759
00:52:56,119 --> 00:52:58,144
Oh, great dogs.

760
00:52:58,755 --> 00:53:00,120
Patti, Maxine...

761
00:53:00,991 --> 00:53:02,151
...and Laverne.

762
00:53:02,860 --> 00:53:05,454
After The Andrews Sisters.

763
00:53:05,529 --> 00:53:08,828
Um, one of them is a boy.

764
00:53:09,333 --> 00:53:11,824
The lady of the house is most insistent...

765
00:53:12,269 --> 00:53:13,736
...in the matter of names.

766
00:53:17,074 --> 00:53:19,474
Good god. When did you get here?

767
00:53:19,943 --> 00:53:21,535
The overnight sleeper.

768
00:53:22,813 --> 00:53:25,407
Central heating and a roof.

769
00:53:26,083 --> 00:53:28,017
Does this mean I'm forgiven?

770
00:53:28,285 --> 00:53:31,118
Absolutely not. I didn't think you'd come.

771
00:53:32,523 --> 00:53:34,514
But we needed a trumpet player.

772
00:53:34,992 --> 00:53:37,187
And I didn't trust you to deliver one.

773
00:53:37,261 --> 00:53:40,526
I wouldn't trust you to deliver
a bottle of semi-skimmed milk.

774
00:53:40,597 --> 00:53:41,962
Thanks so much.

775
00:53:43,300 --> 00:53:44,858
Have you seen Dinah?

776
00:53:44,935 --> 00:53:48,666
Apparently, the lady of the house
doesn't appear in the hours of daylight.

777
00:53:49,172 --> 00:53:51,697
She's probably bricked up
in the west wing.

778
00:53:52,976 --> 00:53:55,536
As soon as the gentleman
has finished his wee dram...

779
00:53:55,612 --> 00:53:57,910
...l'll show him to his accommodation.

780
00:54:12,996 --> 00:54:15,328
We have prepared two bedrooms.

781
00:54:15,399 --> 00:54:19,426
The lady of the house is of the opinion
you'd require only one.

782
00:54:20,237 --> 00:54:23,263
- How many rooms would you be requiring?
- Two, please.

783
00:54:23,574 --> 00:54:26,134
Would they be adjoining
for personal preference?

784
00:54:26,209 --> 00:54:28,939
They should be separated
by a wide stretch of water...

785
00:54:29,012 --> 00:54:31,037
...for personal preference.

786
00:54:33,984 --> 00:54:35,349
Thank you, McNab.

787
00:54:35,819 --> 00:54:37,047
Ma'am.

788
00:54:37,688 --> 00:54:39,781
Thank you, Dinah.
That was a wonderful meal.

789
00:54:39,856 --> 00:54:44,520
- It's a nice little place you've got here.
- I married well and frequently.

790
00:54:45,729 --> 00:54:49,460
But I know all the dirt on me.
I want to know the dirt on you.

791
00:54:50,000 --> 00:54:52,662
Does this mean you've
completed the set, Patrick?

792
00:54:52,736 --> 00:54:55,500
There's no dirt on us.
We're pure as the driven snow.

793
00:54:55,572 --> 00:54:56,971
I hate snow.

794
00:54:57,274 --> 00:54:59,139
It's so goddamned white.

795
00:55:01,912 --> 00:55:04,244
What you mean, completed the set?

796
00:55:05,248 --> 00:55:08,740
He hasn't told you about
the roses on the drum kit?

797
00:55:08,819 --> 00:55:12,619
No, I've tended to go off flowers recently,
as it happens.

798
00:55:13,323 --> 00:55:15,052
Are you going to tell her or shall I?

799
00:55:21,298 --> 00:55:26,258
Well, actually, I got the idea
from the spitfire pilots during the war.

800
00:55:32,876 --> 00:55:37,074
"Pardon me, boy
Is that the Chattanooga choo-choo?

801
00:55:37,848 --> 00:55:39,873
"Track 29

802
00:55:40,617 --> 00:55:43,677
"Boy you can give me a shine

803
00:55:44,888 --> 00:55:48,949
"I can afford
To board the Chattanooga choo-choo

804
00:55:50,060 --> 00:55:52,119
"I got my fare

805
00:55:52,629 --> 00:55:54,494
"And just the travel to spare

806
00:55:55,732 --> 00:55:59,691
"You leave the Pennsylvania station
About a quarter to four

807
00:55:59,870 --> 00:56:02,896
"Read a magazine
And then you're in Baltimore

808
00:56:03,040 --> 00:56:05,804
"Dinner in a diner
Nothing could be finer

809
00:56:05,976 --> 00:56:08,706
"Than to have your ham and eggs
In Carolina

810
00:56:09,079 --> 00:56:11,513
"When you hear the whistle
Blowing into the bar

811
00:56:12,215 --> 00:56:14,979
"Then you know that Tennessee
Is not very far

812
00:56:15,152 --> 00:56:17,985
"Shove a lot of coal in
Got to keep it rollin'

813
00:56:18,855 --> 00:56:20,914
"Chattanooga, there you are"

814
00:56:24,995 --> 00:56:26,963
Yeah, he screwed the lot of us.

815
00:56:27,264 --> 00:56:29,926
I looked upon it
as my contribution to the war effort.

816
00:56:30,000 --> 00:56:31,467
And what about the fight?

817
00:56:31,535 --> 00:56:35,096
Never mind about the adolescent
sex and the fights. What about the music?

818
00:56:36,273 --> 00:56:40,004
What you tell me is that
the Blonde Bombshell reunion band...

819
00:56:40,077 --> 00:56:41,908
...thus far comprises you two...

820
00:56:42,279 --> 00:56:44,440
...a foul-mouthed piano player...

821
00:56:44,514 --> 00:56:47,244
...an alto player out
of the slammer on bail...

822
00:56:47,317 --> 00:56:49,911
...a trombone player in the arms of Jesus...

823
00:56:50,220 --> 00:56:52,484
...a de facto lunatic, two corpses...

824
00:56:52,556 --> 00:56:54,956
...and a singer who won't
show up on the night.

825
00:56:55,425 --> 00:56:57,620
And not forgetting your lovely self.

826
00:56:59,996 --> 00:57:01,088
Do you still play?

827
00:57:02,632 --> 00:57:04,122
Do I still play?

828
00:57:07,137 --> 00:57:08,798
A little story.

829
00:57:09,272 --> 00:57:12,708
My grandson plays trumpet
in his high school band...

830
00:57:13,143 --> 00:57:14,974
...in Boston, Massachusetts.

831
00:57:15,312 --> 00:57:18,543
On a recent visit
to Grandma's magic castle...

832
00:57:18,615 --> 00:57:20,549
...in downtown Brigadoon.

833
00:57:21,318 --> 00:57:22,945
He consulted me.

834
00:57:23,320 --> 00:57:25,686
I gave him a lesson, and guess what?

835
00:57:25,756 --> 00:57:28,691
I can still blow this thing.
I can still part the waters...

836
00:57:28,759 --> 00:57:31,159
...and bring down the walls of the city.

837
00:57:47,010 --> 00:57:48,602
That's seriously brilliant.

838
00:57:56,753 --> 00:58:00,849
Sadly, the lady is an officially
recognized alcoholic.

839
00:58:01,291 --> 00:58:03,759
- Does this often happen?
- Every night.

840
00:58:03,827 --> 00:58:05,954
But she knows she is an alcoholic.

841
00:58:06,229 --> 00:58:10,290
And apparently that's the first step
towards a cure.

842
00:58:10,667 --> 00:58:14,159
- How long has it been going on?
- Since the Second World War.

843
00:58:15,038 --> 00:58:17,302
An unhappy love affair, seemingly.

844
00:58:19,976 --> 00:58:23,241
- Men can be swine.
- So I'm led to believe.

845
00:58:30,020 --> 00:58:31,282
Elizabeth.

846
00:58:32,122 --> 00:58:33,282
What?

847
00:58:35,625 --> 00:58:37,354
I need to ask you something.

848
00:58:37,427 --> 00:58:38,724
Patrick.

849
00:58:38,795 --> 00:58:40,456
Mind if I sit down?

850
00:58:41,264 --> 00:58:43,198
It's been a long day.

851
00:58:43,767 --> 00:58:46,668
And I'm not cold and I'm not frightened.

852
00:58:46,803 --> 00:58:50,170
And there are no bombs falling.
Scotland's not at war.

853
00:58:50,907 --> 00:58:53,375
And I have no intention
of completing your set.

854
00:58:53,443 --> 00:58:55,604
What's it like being a woman?

855
00:58:56,680 --> 00:58:58,113
What?

856
00:58:58,381 --> 00:59:01,179
Well, sit down.

857
00:59:03,353 --> 00:59:07,585
Well, you see, the last weeks
I've relived quite a lot of my past life.

858
00:59:08,291 --> 00:59:10,885
Most of it seems to have
been a bit of a shambles.

859
00:59:11,294 --> 00:59:13,262
Well, that was well spotted.

860
00:59:13,330 --> 00:59:16,629
And I think quite a lot of that
shambles could have been avoided...

861
00:59:16,700 --> 00:59:19,533
...if I'd tried a bit harder
to understand women.

862
00:59:20,804 --> 00:59:24,001
Which is odd since I pretended
to be one for so long.

863
00:59:25,008 --> 00:59:26,202
But...

864
00:59:27,077 --> 00:59:28,874
Well, that doesn't really help.

865
00:59:28,945 --> 00:59:31,812
I mean, women...
Well, you're different, aren't you?

866
00:59:32,148 --> 00:59:35,777
Yes, we have babies and husbands
and washing machines.

867
00:59:39,356 --> 00:59:41,119
I see your family...

868
00:59:41,825 --> 00:59:44,953
...and I see three generations
of women and it's lovely.

869
00:59:47,030 --> 00:59:49,055
Wish I had generations.

870
00:59:50,700 --> 00:59:53,669
Much too late for that.
It's too late for everything.

871
00:59:54,971 --> 00:59:56,632
No, not everything.

872
00:59:57,607 --> 00:59:59,370
But I'm going to bed now.

873
01:00:01,645 --> 01:00:03,169
Why did you marry George?

874
01:00:05,482 --> 01:00:08,713
Patrick, you know what it was like.

875
01:00:10,253 --> 01:00:12,881
When I was a young woman,
your soul purpose in life...

876
01:00:12,956 --> 01:00:15,516
...was to get engaged
to a young man with prospects.

877
01:00:15,592 --> 01:00:17,822
So, I did. I met him at a staff dance.

878
01:00:17,894 --> 01:00:19,794
A dance. What was the band like?

879
01:00:19,863 --> 01:00:21,330
Oh, lousy.

880
01:00:22,699 --> 01:00:26,135
Jimmy Dickenson, and his Rhythm Rascals.

881
01:00:26,236 --> 01:00:28,500
I was a rhythm rascal once.

882
01:00:30,840 --> 01:00:32,865
Now I'm serious and responsible.

883
01:00:35,078 --> 01:00:37,171
And I think I'm in love with you.

884
01:00:39,316 --> 01:00:41,409
No, you're not.

885
01:00:42,052 --> 01:00:45,146
You're just cold and frightened.

886
01:00:52,729 --> 01:00:54,697
- Goodnight, Patrick.
- Goodnight.

887
01:01:21,257 --> 01:01:23,691
Nice doggies.
Stay home and look after the lady.

888
01:01:23,760 --> 01:01:26,888
She's a fine musician,
but she's not very well.

889
01:01:30,233 --> 01:01:32,599
Hey! Where the hell are you guys going?

890
01:01:34,004 --> 01:01:35,869
London, we've got a gig.

891
01:01:35,972 --> 01:01:38,907
And I'm held prisoner here against my will.

892
01:01:39,075 --> 01:01:41,043
Wait, I'm coming down!

893
01:01:41,144 --> 01:01:43,237
God, she's coming with us.

894
01:01:43,813 --> 01:01:47,214
- What should we do, head for the hills?
- These are the hills.

895
01:02:01,598 --> 01:02:03,793
SCHOOL DANCE

896
01:02:17,113 --> 01:02:19,138
Stage management, up the ladder.

897
01:02:19,382 --> 01:02:22,783
Hi, guys.
Sound check in 10 minutes, okay?

898
01:02:24,120 --> 01:02:25,644
There you go.

899
01:02:26,322 --> 01:02:27,949
Well, this is it, D-Day.

900
01:02:28,058 --> 01:02:30,458
- Are you nervous?
- No, terrified.

901
01:02:35,999 --> 01:02:37,125
Any news on Dinah?

902
01:02:37,200 --> 01:02:39,668
Yes, she's happily ensconced
in the Savoy Hotel.

903
01:02:39,736 --> 01:02:41,226
We saw her at breakfast.

904
01:02:41,671 --> 01:02:43,662
She planned to order a small distillery...

905
01:02:43,740 --> 01:02:47,039
...from room service for later on.
- Oh, god.

906
01:02:47,110 --> 01:02:50,477
I'm in charge of catering
and Leslie's doing decorations.

907
01:02:50,647 --> 01:02:52,911
Hi, Leslie. You're working well.

908
01:02:52,982 --> 01:02:54,643
The decor's gonna be a wow.

909
01:02:54,717 --> 01:02:56,912
Oh, I don't really like wows.

910
01:02:57,654 --> 01:03:00,282
Hey, what manner of place is this?

911
01:03:00,490 --> 01:03:03,050
This is where we're gonna
make sweet music.

912
01:03:03,359 --> 01:03:04,690
Forget it, she's here.

913
01:03:04,761 --> 01:03:07,321
- Evelyn!
- Dinah!

914
01:03:08,064 --> 01:03:12,262
- You're looking good for a jailbird.
- I've been rehabilitated.

915
01:03:12,435 --> 01:03:13,697
Annie!

916
01:03:15,472 --> 01:03:17,838
Dinah, good to see you.

917
01:03:18,408 --> 01:03:19,432
Betty.

918
01:03:19,509 --> 01:03:21,443
Glad you could make it, Dinah.

919
01:03:22,512 --> 01:03:26,471
- The famous roses.
- Oh, him and his bloody roses.

920
01:03:26,616 --> 01:03:30,552
Just for the record, mine is quite definitely
there under false pretenses.

921
01:03:30,620 --> 01:03:33,350
I'd been drinking.
I don't remember very much about it.

922
01:03:33,423 --> 01:03:36,017
Far as I can recall,
it was deeply embarrassing...

923
01:03:36,092 --> 01:03:37,821
...and desperately quick.

924
01:03:37,894 --> 01:03:40,886
It was horrible. I try not to think about it.

925
01:03:41,498 --> 01:03:44,228
I haven't seen you guys since the big fight.

926
01:03:44,300 --> 01:03:46,860
Look. Will somebody tell me
about the big fight?

927
01:03:46,936 --> 01:03:49,530
It was the day we were
gonna play for the Yanks.

928
01:03:49,606 --> 01:03:52,837
You couldn't come.
They wouldn't allow you off school.

929
01:04:00,350 --> 01:04:01,647
Hey, sweet cakes!

930
01:04:01,718 --> 01:04:03,083
I love Americans.

931
01:04:05,755 --> 01:04:07,723
Hey, blondie, over here!

932
01:04:07,957 --> 01:04:09,925
Marry me, I love you!

933
01:04:11,227 --> 01:04:12,785
Girls, calm down.

934
01:04:13,596 --> 01:04:15,655
- Hi, girls.
- Hello.

935
01:04:15,999 --> 01:04:18,263
Welcome to New Jersey on Thames.

936
01:04:18,501 --> 01:04:21,026
- It's a pleasure to be here.
- A pleasure to be here.

937
01:04:21,104 --> 01:04:26,064
Well, that remains to be seen.
We've got a slight technical difficulty.

938
01:04:30,380 --> 01:04:32,211
- This is it.
- Watch your heels, girls.

939
01:04:32,282 --> 01:04:33,943
Welcome to our social club.

940
01:04:34,484 --> 01:04:35,883
- Careful, Dinah.
- What happened?

941
01:04:35,952 --> 01:04:39,911
- So much for our big night.
- A doodle bug. A flying bomb.

942
01:04:40,290 --> 01:04:43,259
- I hope we still get paid.
- The guys were real disappointed.

943
01:04:43,326 --> 01:04:45,055
They heard you on the radio.

944
01:04:45,128 --> 01:04:48,655
And they found out you all were dames,
you can imagine.

945
01:04:48,731 --> 01:04:50,858
I'm the one who's disappointed.

946
01:04:51,000 --> 01:04:53,127
That's the lady from the bathroom.

947
01:04:53,570 --> 01:04:55,561
- Hey, girls.
- Darling boy.

948
01:04:55,638 --> 01:04:57,538
Put that man down. He's mine!

949
01:04:57,640 --> 01:04:58,868
No, he isn't.

950
01:04:58,942 --> 01:05:02,139
Patrick and I are secretly engaged.
And I want everyone to know it.

951
01:05:02,212 --> 01:05:04,874
Well, I got some news.
He's actually engaged to me.

952
01:05:04,948 --> 01:05:06,347
He's even met my mother.

953
01:05:06,416 --> 01:05:09,476
Sorry, girls, he's marrying me
as soon as the war's over.

954
01:05:09,552 --> 01:05:12,043
I just bought a silk nightie
on the black market.

955
01:05:12,121 --> 01:05:13,247
He's marrying me.

956
01:05:13,323 --> 01:05:15,791
I spoke to the vicar
and he gave me some booklets.

957
01:05:15,858 --> 01:05:18,793
He proposed to me.
In the boiler house on Tuesday.

958
01:05:19,028 --> 01:05:21,155
He proposed to me on Thursday.

959
01:05:21,231 --> 01:05:24,257
You're all wasting your time.
Patrick's already married to me.

960
01:05:24,334 --> 01:05:25,824
- Come on.
- Please.

961
01:05:25,902 --> 01:05:27,733
We got married this morning.

962
01:05:28,338 --> 01:05:30,772
- You lying bitch.
- Tell them, dear.

963
01:05:31,574 --> 01:05:33,508
- Yes, tell us.
- You lied to us.

964
01:05:34,444 --> 01:05:36,912
Tell us. Go on, what's all this rubbish?

965
01:05:36,980 --> 01:05:41,610
It's true. I got a 48-hour pass
so I could get married and play the gig.

966
01:05:42,285 --> 01:05:44,515
Anyway, tomorrow I go off to foreign parts.

967
01:05:44,587 --> 01:05:46,782
- Lf you live that long.
- He won't.

968
01:05:53,396 --> 01:05:54,795
Well, how was it?

969
01:05:56,065 --> 01:05:58,659
- You tell them.
- Dinah, you were sharp.

970
01:05:59,102 --> 01:06:01,332
Evie, you were flat.

971
01:06:01,437 --> 01:06:05,203
And Annie, you were in tune,
but you've forgotten how to swing.

972
01:06:06,042 --> 01:06:09,170
And Patrick, you sound like
you're wearing a surgical boot.

973
01:06:09,245 --> 01:06:11,577
- What about me?
- Oh, you were fine, darling.

974
01:06:11,648 --> 01:06:14,344
- She would say that. You're her favorite.
- Oh, please.

975
01:06:14,417 --> 01:06:16,408
- Girls, girls.
- Oh, shut up!

976
01:06:16,486 --> 01:06:18,386
Go screw yourself.

977
01:06:18,888 --> 01:06:22,119
That's as individuals.
As a unit, we were crap.

978
01:06:22,292 --> 01:06:24,954
Maybe we were crap way back in 1944...

979
01:06:25,061 --> 01:06:26,585
...except in our dreams.

980
01:06:26,663 --> 01:06:30,497
Hey, and that's another thing.
There's to be no drinking on the stand.

981
01:06:30,700 --> 01:06:33,430
Sorry, babe. This is not negotiable.

982
01:06:33,503 --> 01:06:36,199
Sober, I can't play a note.
Drunk, I can't play a note.

983
01:06:36,272 --> 01:06:39,503
But there's a point in the middle
where I play like a goddamn angel.

984
01:06:39,575 --> 01:06:42,703
Please, Dinah, do you mind?
I'd rather you didn't blaspheme.

985
01:06:43,413 --> 01:06:45,005
This is a bandstand, sister.

986
01:06:45,081 --> 01:06:48,016
If you don't like it,
get thee to a fucking nunnery.

987
01:06:48,985 --> 01:06:50,213
That's enough!

988
01:06:50,520 --> 01:06:51,544
I resign!

989
01:06:51,854 --> 01:06:52,912
I resign!

990
01:06:53,556 --> 01:06:55,148
You can't do that.

991
01:06:55,658 --> 01:06:57,091
Shit, I resign too.

992
01:06:57,160 --> 01:06:59,094
- Girls.
- Me too.

993
01:07:01,931 --> 01:07:05,059
I'm going back to the prison.
At least people are nice in prison.

994
01:07:10,406 --> 01:07:11,498
Come back.

995
01:07:12,075 --> 01:07:14,839
Your husband just dropped
the bomb on the band, lady.

996
01:07:15,945 --> 01:07:17,936
Stop, you're not going anywhere!

997
01:07:18,081 --> 01:07:19,946
You lot, you're a disgrace to women.

998
01:07:20,016 --> 01:07:21,608
I wouldn't disagree with that.

999
01:07:21,684 --> 01:07:25,950
- Don't you realize what's at stake here?
- What's at stake? I can't think of anything.

1000
01:07:26,255 --> 01:07:28,587
First off, the dance is in an hour's time.

1001
01:07:28,658 --> 01:07:32,321
There's 100 quid in it for you.
I had to fight the committee to get it.

1002
01:07:32,829 --> 01:07:35,798
- Is that 100 pounds each?
- No, between you to share.

1003
01:07:35,865 --> 01:07:37,127
And tea and biscuits.

1004
01:07:37,633 --> 01:07:40,659
If I give you 100 pounds,
may I proceed peacefully...

1005
01:07:40,737 --> 01:07:42,398
...to the nearest liquor store?

1006
