Only because we thought you were dead.

1016
01:08:10,366 --> 01:08:11,958
I'm very much alive.

1017
01:08:13,102 --> 01:08:15,593
Not so sure about the rest of you, though.

1018
01:08:18,941 --> 01:08:20,306
Elizabeth!

1019
01:08:24,480 --> 01:08:26,038
And Patrick.

1020
01:08:27,316 --> 01:08:28,476
Patrick.

1021
01:08:29,619 --> 01:08:32,247
The man who was going to marry me.

1022
01:08:36,459 --> 01:08:37,790
Now we can rehearse.

1023
01:09:43,326 --> 01:09:45,817
Apparently they're called Open Wound.

1024
01:09:46,195 --> 01:09:48,288
- Open what?
- Wound.

1025
01:09:49,365 --> 01:09:52,493
And the music they play is retro punk.

1026
01:09:53,202 --> 01:09:56,296
Well, I can't tell whether
this is any good or not.

1027
01:09:57,039 --> 01:09:59,064
I think we might be in the wrong place.

1028
01:09:59,141 --> 01:10:01,939
I think we might be
in the wrong bleeding century.

1029
01:10:12,955 --> 01:10:17,221
I will be good for the rest of my life
if you help me get through this, please.

1030
01:10:24,901 --> 01:10:26,960
- Any news of Gwen?
- Not as yet.

1031
01:10:28,170 --> 01:10:30,138
She doesn't show, we'll kill her.

1032
01:10:30,206 --> 01:10:32,037
You'll see to it. Right, babe?

1033
01:10:32,108 --> 01:10:35,475
There's a geezer comes in the bar.
He's in that line of work.

1034
01:10:35,678 --> 01:10:37,407
I know how to kill people.

1035
01:10:38,714 --> 01:10:41,342
Do you really know how to kill people?

1036
01:10:42,318 --> 01:10:44,980
It was necessary in the Resistance.

1037
